00:09:14.310 --> 00:09:17.630
Yes, I mean, well, it's funny.

00:09:17.630 --> 00:09:21.140
I had a voice teacher and
I still study to this day,

00:09:21.140 --> 00:09:24.250 position:56%
but this voice teacher -- I remember
I was singing at Carnegie Hall,

00:09:24.250 --> 00:09:26.250
and I was doing some of
these songs from The Hill,

00:09:26.250 --> 00:09:29.220
and I didn't have a microphone,
and you know it was so beautiful,

00:09:29.220 --> 00:09:32.160
the voice in acoustic
space which I really love.

00:09:32.160 --> 00:09:35.240
And he, a voice teacher of all
things, you know, opera teacher

00:09:35.240 --> 00:09:37.540
and everything, he said,
you should use a microphone

00:09:37.540 --> 00:09:40.820
because then you get to hear
the little nuances and clicks

00:09:40.820 --> 00:09:46.030
so you know -- or the little,
